<item>
            <title>[HIVE-28190] Materialized view rebuild lock heart-beating is broken</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HIVE-28190</link>
                <project id="12310843" key="HIVE">Hive</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;It fails with the following error:&#160;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
org.springframework.dao.InvalidDataAccessApiUsageException: SQL [UPDATE &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;MATERIALIZATION_REBUILD_LOCKS&quot;&lt;/span&gt; SET &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;MRL_LAST_HEARTBEAT&quot;&lt;/span&gt; = 1712571919559 WHERE &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;MRL_TXN_ID&quot;&lt;/span&gt; = 2297 AND &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;MRL_DB_NAME&quot;&lt;/span&gt; = ? AND &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;MRL_TBL_NAME&quot;&lt;/span&gt; = ?]: given 2 parameters but expected 0 &lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We didn&apos;t spot it so far as when the heartbeat of materialized view fails with an error, it doesn&apos;t affect the rebuild query run. So that it can be only spotted by actively watching the logs.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
